          <text>
                    <body>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName>
                                        <date>20<hi rend="sup">th</hi> April 5607</date>.</p>
                              <p>[Hebrew]</p>
                              <p>My Dear Sir,</p>
                              <p>It is not long since, several of my friends <del>have</del> urged
                                        me to come out<lb/> publicly, in your periodical, with my
                                        opinion about the [Hebrew] which<lb/> are yearly brought
                                        form the <placeName>West Indies</placeName> to this country.
                                                  <del>So</del> much <add>so I am</add> disinclined
                                                  <del>am I</del> to give publicity to any thing of
                                        a <del>disputatious</del>
                                        <add>controversial</add><lb/> nature in matters of our
                                        religion that I should not even now trouble<lb/> you, but
                                        that the time is approaching when our yearly
                                        communications<lb/> are made to the <del>W. I.</del>
                                        <add><placeName>West Indies</placeName> for the new supply
                                                  of citizens</add> and I think it
                                                  <add>therefore</add> my duty, for the sake of our
                                        religion<lb/> to state that these [Hebrew] are [Hebrew]
                                        there cannot be found any word<lb/> against <del>it</del>
                                        <add>them</add> in [Hebrew]. All rumours that were set
                                        afloat<lb/> against the [Hebrew] of these are founded in
                                        error misinformation.<lb/> Now, my Dear Sir, I do not intend
                                        to injure the feelings of any<lb/> of our learned men; I
                                        wish only the unity of Israel in matters<lb/> of religious
                                        observances, and that our <sic>brethern</sic> of Israel
                                        shall not<lb/> be <sic>wilfully</sic> deprived from [Hebrew]
                                        without just cause.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">I remain, very respectfully</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">Your obedient servant</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <persName role="author">A. Rice</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>To the <addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee></p>
                    </body>
